cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with linear codes over finite fields and their generalization to a specific ring. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of combinatorial properties of codes, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of new codes using the generalized LCD codes involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and the analysis of their parameters falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
